Problem 4: Number Comparison with Arithmetic Result
Take two numbers as input.
Perform:
• Addition
• Multiplication
Check:
• Sum greater than product OR both numbers equal
Print suitable messages.


#!bin/bash
read -p "Enter first number : " num1
read -p "Enter second number : " num2
sum=$(($num1+$num2))
product=$(($num1*$num2))        
if [[ $sum -gt $product || $num1 -eq $num2 ]];
then
    echo "Sum is greater than product OR both numbers are equal"
else
    echo "Product is greater than sum AND both numbers are not equal"
fi
